title: gdb stack traces for libtorch are missing debug symbols
body_html:
Example:

(gdb) up
#1  0x00007fffd7130d80 in torch::barf(char const*, ...) () from /data/users/zdevito/pytorch/torch/lib/libtorch.so.1
(gdb)
#2  0x00007fffd70e237d in torch::jit::IValue::toTensor() && [clone .part.171] () from /data/users/zdevito/pytorch/torch/lib/libtorch.so.1
(gdb)
#3  0x00007fffd745e975 in torch::jit::GraphExecutorImpl::run(torch::jit::variable_tensor_list) () from /data/users/zdevito/pytorch/torch/lib/libtorch.so.1
(gdb)
#4  0x00007fffd7459c37 in torch::jit::GraphExecutor::run(torch::jit::variable_tensor_list&&) () from /data/users/zdevito/pytorch/torch/lib/libtorch.so.1
(gdb)
#5  0x00007fffe7c1bf0c in torch::jit::script::Method::run (inputs=..., this=0x1a77700) at /data/users/zdevito/pytorch/torch/csrc/jit/script/module.h:60
60	    return get_executor().run(std::move(inputs));
(gdb)
#6  torch::jit::script::runMethodFromPython (m=..., args=...) at torch/csrc/jit/script/init.cpp:359
359	  auto outputs = m.run(std::move(inputs));

Note that files like script/init.cpp which are still part of _C.so have debug symbols. This makes it extremely hard to debug anything.

body:
Example:
```
(gdb) up
#1  0x00007fffd7130d80 in torch::barf(char const*, ...) () from /data/users/zdevito/pytorch/torch/lib/libtorch.so.1
(gdb)
#2  0x00007fffd70e237d in torch::jit::IValue::toTensor() && [clone .part.171] () from /data/users/zdevito/pytorch/torch/lib/libtorch.so.1
(gdb)
#3  0x00007fffd745e975 in torch::jit::GraphExecutorImpl::run(torch::jit::variable_tensor_list) () from /data/users/zdevito/pytorch/torch/lib/libtorch.so.1
(gdb)
#4  0x00007fffd7459c37 in torch::jit::GraphExecutor::run(torch::jit::variable_tensor_list&&) () from /data/users/zdevito/pytorch/torch/lib/libtorch.so.1
(gdb)
#5  0x00007fffe7c1bf0c in torch::jit::script::Method::run (inputs=..., this=0x1a77700) at /data/users/zdevito/pytorch/torch/csrc/jit/script/module.h:60
60	    return get_executor().run(std::move(inputs));
(gdb)
#6  torch::jit::script::runMethodFromPython (m=..., args=...) at torch/csrc/jit/script/init.cpp:359
359	  auto outputs = m.run(std::move(inputs));
```
Note that files like `script/init.cpp` which are still part of _C.so have debug symbols. This makes it extremely hard to debug anything.
